6. Custodian Rugpull.

Your custodian might decide to exit scam you and steal your #bitcoin. Yes, you can go after them legally, but wouldn't it be better to just avoid the possibility altogether?

3. Paper Bitcoin.

Many exchanges are incentivized to encourage users to leave the #bitcoin on their exchange so that they can run a fractional reserve system where there is more paper bitcoin than real bitcoin.

2. Privacy.

When a custodian holds your #bitcoin for you, it's much easier for them to surveil you and compromise your privacy. It is trivial for your custodian to see all transactions you perform with your bitcoin.
